Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Fill and boil your #kettle{}.

Trim the @aubergine{1}, then cut into small pieces. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and
discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1/2} into small pieces. Peel and grate the
@garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the aubergine and pepper onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil,
season with @salt and @black pepper, then sprinkle over half the
@Italian style herbs{1}.

Use your hands to coat the veg in the herbs, then spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and golden, ~{20-25%mins}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an
> ovenproof dish before baking.

Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90} and fry until golden, ~{1-2%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Add the onion and fry until soft, ~{4-5%mins}.

Stir in the @sun-dried tomato paste{25}, garlic and remaining Italian style
herbs. Cook for ~{1%min}, then stir in the @risotto rice{175} and cook until the
edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook lardons thoroughly.

Add the @boiled water for the risotto{450} and @vegetable stock paste{20} to the
pan. Stir to combine.

Bring back up to the boil, then pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with
#foil{}) and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and
the water has been absorbed, ~{20-25%mins}.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and mix in the
@butter{20} and @grated hard Italian style cheese{40}.

Stir through the roasted aubergine and pepper.

Season to taste with salt and pepper if needed, adding a splash of water if it's
a little dry.

Share the ratatouille risotto between your bowls and serve with a handful of
@wild rocket{20} on top.

Enjoy!